Description: Oval handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine orange-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a, 28? Name Archembrotos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0701.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1096)
